<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-08-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-08-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="1784" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1784">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 819.74/57.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Price</persName> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Panama</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-08-23">
                                    <hi rend="italic">August 23, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Referring to my cable of August 14, Department’s telegram August 17. We
                            have taken and are exercising complete control of wireless <pb facs="1165" n="1049" xml:id="pg_1049"/> pursuant to verbal authority
                            from Panama; but the decree of Panaman President assured me for August
                            14 was submitted only last Tuesday. It gave only temporary control
                            during the crisis in Europe. Under my protest its publication was
                            withheld and Panaman Minister for Foreign Affairs agreed to have it
                            reformed, granting complete and permanent control in accordance with
                            prior assurances.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Price</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>